item.title: [SCB-6] Have linkhunter know about mime types
item.description:
LinkHunter needs to be able to ignore certain links. No point scanning a binary file for a <a etc.

Maybe it could do it based on binary versus text? Only work on mime types that start with txt or plain.
item.summary: Have linkhunter know about mime types

comments.comment: The code is now in. It ignores non-ascii mime types currently rather than using lazy loading.
